A grainy 1980s Soviet-era VHS commercial for “Krazy Ivan’s Fried Chick-Chick.” Tape glitches, warped colors, flickering tracking lines. Krazy Ivan stands in a cold concrete food hall under a buzzing red star sign. He presents an enormous chicken sampler on a dented metal tray.  Audio crackles as Ivan delivers his line with stern Soviet pride:
“At Krazy Ivan’s Fried Chick-Chick… the crunch is strong… the flavor is stronger… and the portions? Completely insane!”
Quick VHS montage: shaky close-up of crispy chicken bite, sizzling chicken in blown-out lighting, and a brief low-budget shot of cartoon chickens doing a Cossack dance.  Final freeze-frame on Ivan holding the sampler.  Deadpan narrator: “Krazy Ivan’s Fried Chick-Chick — Approved by the Ministry of Deliciousness.”  Logo appears with VHS warping and a warbly balalaika sting.
